&lt;p&gt;As a Principal Game Designer, you will design, tweak, and optimize the player experience. Your analytical skills, player insight, and creativity aid in crafting in- and out-of-game experiences that engage and surprise players. You will collaborate with interdisciplinary teams and work with every tool at hand to innovate and iterate player-focused designs that&#39;ll delight millions around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://playvalorant.com/en-us/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VALORANT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is Riot’s take on a character-based tactical shooter. As a &lt;strong&gt;Principal Game Designer&lt;/strong&gt; on the &lt;strong&gt;Competitive Systems team&lt;/strong&gt;, you’ll help shape and define how players engage with competition across ranked, matchmaking, and adjacent systems that influence mastery, fairness, and long-term growth. You’ll partner with product managers, engineers, analysts, and other designers to develop systems that are strategically sound, motivating to engage with, and worthy of players’ investment over time. You have significant competitive multiplayer affinity and experience, understanding the challenges players encounter and the motivations that drive them. You are comfortable operating in ambiguous spaces and can design and iterate on solutions to complex systemic problems. This role reports to the Lead Metasystems Designer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve competitive systems that reward player skill, growth, and long-term investment in VALORANT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the design of ranked, matchmaking, and adjacent competitive systems to support fairness, competitive integrity, and player engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with product managers, engineers, analysts, and design leadership to ensure systems are cohesive, consistent, and in line with VALORANT’s overall vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep the focus on player value by leveraging feedback, research, and game data to iterate on designs and improve the competitive experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create multiple design solutions and clearly articulate the trade-offs, risks, and player impact of each.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide direction, mentorship, and feedback to other designers, fostering collaboration and craft excellence across systems design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Playtest VALORANT regularly and help push improvements for existing systems and new concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in professional Game Design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep experience developing competitive multiplayer systems such as matchmaking, ranked, and skill systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shipped or contributed to at least one AAA+ online competitive title.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to design and iterate on complex systems with a clear understanding of player impact and downstream effects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills with proven ability to articulate design rationale, trade-offs, and decision frameworks to cross-disciplinary partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a live-service development environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Desired Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep passion for and understanding of competitive online games and their player communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with online shooters, especially VALORANT or tactical shooters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience balancing competitive integrity with engaging and rewarding systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a senior craft leader or thought partner on materially impactful design initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to interpret and learn from charged or emotional player feedback to improve the product experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing across multiple platforms, including PC, console, or mobile.&lt;/li&g

&lt;p&gt;As a Game Designer, you will design, tweak, and optimize the player experience. Your analytical skills, player insight, and creativity aid in crafting in- and out-of-game experiences that engage and surprise players. You will collaborate with interdisciplinary teams and work with every tool at hand to innovate and iterate player-focused designs that&#39;ll delight millions around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Manager of Game Design&lt;/strong&gt; on League of Legends, you’ll lead a group of passionate designers as we set up League of Legends for its next 10 years, reporting to the Design Director for League of Legends. You’ll partner with discipline leads across the studio to ensure a well managed and staffed discipline, that designers have well supported growth, and that craft execution meets or exceeds our extremely high standards. You’ll make significant contributions to wider Design Department processes and rituals. You’ll also help mentor designers and design managers across League of Legends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead game design for new projects, features, and content on League of Legends, ensuring the vision, strategy, and execution align with player expectations, Riot’s design values, and the game leadership team’s overall product strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide and mentor designers, setting clear goals, providing continuous feedback, and fostering an environment of creativity, innovation, and professional development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring design craft standards are upheld across League of Legends, contribute to Design Department processes and rituals, leveling up our approach to things like recruiting, performance assessment and knowledge sharing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams—including art, product management, engineering, and publishing—to craft resonant experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balance player feedback, data insights, and business objectives to make informed design decisions that deliver on League of Legends’ promise of competitive and rewarding gameplay.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent and advocate for the design discipline both internally to other teams and externally to players.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build positive relationships across other teams at Riot in shared gameplay spaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in game design roles in game development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience as a leader in a game design organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working as a developer on a PVP game.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in managing a significant team of designers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated and substantial experience recruiting new designers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a “games as a service” environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Desired Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge and intimate understanding of the League of Legends game experience and what approaches to design best meet its players’ needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on MOBA or competitive multiplayer titles, with an understanding of core gameplay loops and player motivations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with data analysis and the ability to leverage insights from user research, telemetry, and other metrics to inform design decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For this role, you&#39;ll find success through craft expertise and a collaborative spirit that prioritizes the delight of players. We will look at your past studies and experience, but for this role, we also look for dedicated people with a personal relationship with games. If you embody player empathy and care about players&#39; experiences, this is the role for you!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Perks:&lt;/st

&lt;p&gt;Scopely is looking for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Lead/Manager Economy and Systems Designer &lt;/strong&gt;to join the Looney Tunes game team. The position can be based in India (preferably Bangalore) or Tel Aviv, Israel or Barcelona, Spain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we care deeply about what we do and want to inspire play, every day - whether in our work environments alongside our talented colleagues, or through our deep connections with our communities of players. We are a global team of game lovers who are developing, publishing and innovating the mobile games industry, connecting millions of people around the world daily.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Looney Tunes: World of Mayhem team embraces the &quot;One Team, One Dream&quot; culture every day. Everybody is empowered to work with a high level of autonomy and ownership to deliver the best possible player experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Lead/Manager Economy &amp;amp; Systems Designer&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be responsible for shaping the economy and gameplay systems of Looney Tunes: World of Mayhem. You will ensure a balance between engaging progression, sustainable monetization, and deep, satisfying systems that keep players returning over a long lifecycle. This is a senior role requiring strong collaboration, systems thinking, and a deep understanding of the mobile F2P space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Economy &amp;amp; Progression Design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and optimize in-game economies - including currencies, pricing models, existing systems, upcoming features, and progression paths - from early player onboarding through elder player end-game - to drive long-term engagement and maximize revenue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct segmentation analysis and craft economy models tailored to different user archetypes and LTV tiers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;​​Define economy KPIs and build mathematical models &amp;amp; simulations to monitor, predict and validate the impact of features on game balance and player behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Game Design Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own feature development from pitch to live operation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain complete understanding and ownership of back-end Admin tool for game configurations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement and balance new features and systems: Combat systems, Player progression, Game Modes and feature loops&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design of tools and workflows that enable scalable live operations and event-driven gameplay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate clear feature documentation, user flows, diagrams, wireframes, and/or prototypes for new features and systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze game data and player behavior to iterate and evolve live features&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the product team, Engineers, Artists &amp;amp; LiveOps to design the optimal daily experience for our players, and deliver impactful features&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and support junior designers on economy and systems design best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence the product roadmap with innovative, data-informed design proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in mobile F2P game design with a focus on economy and systems design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated expertise in crafting game features, systems, and economies on at least one shipped live-operated game, preferably RPG or strategy-based&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience modelling/maintaining complex Economies (MMO, Strategy-MMO, RPG)&lt;/li&

